The paper deals with the complexity of solving parity games, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). The analysis of complexity measures for directed graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
